        ],
        [
          "Regression",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Final  Exam Grade",
          "Grade: 0 to 10",
          "1073 undergradaute learners",
          "1 Introduction to Informatics",
          "LMS logs, SIS, Assignment Scores",
          "[Gender, New Student, Ocsi, Wrii, Logins, Pseudocode Forum views, Module forum views, Course forum views, Viewws of course news, Posts in Pseudo-Code Forum, Posts in Compiler forum, Posts in Module forum, Posts in Course Forum]",
          "8 stages of the academic year",
          "Categoricals are One-Hot Encoded and the data was subsequently normalized.\n\nThe academic year was split into 8 partitions and the authors collect the data for each period (Ocs and Wri have 4)\n\nAuthors use 3 kNN base regressors using self-training.\n\n",
          "Linear Regression, MSSRA, IBk, M5Rules, M5 Model Tree, Random Forest, SMOreg",
          "10-fold cross-Validation",
          "Friedman Rank:\n{MAE:  7.625 - MSSRA, RAE: 7.00 - MSSRA, RMSE: 8.00 - MSSRA,  PCC: 8.125 - MSSRA}",
          "Authors present a novel frameworkk for Semi-Supervised Regression called MSSRA.\n\nAuthors keep performance for each period - SMO outperforms all others on the first 2 partitions, but MSSRA outperforms all others past that point. \n\nMore adata leads to better predictions as usual.\n\nAuthors also test different ratios of labeled data in their dataset, showing that it is possible to obtain good results with as little as 10 to 15% of labeled data.",
          "Small sample size. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
